<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1937</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Clerk <persName type="to">Brewer</persName>, in charge of the
                                Legation archives</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your October 24 and 26. Do you think American forces have situation
                            sufficiently under control to prevent future outbreaks without
                            declaration martial law? Would immediate declaration martial law in
                            capital or throughout Republic have satisfactory or unsatisfactory
                            effect on present situation?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>